=== Operational finding: load_model heap-OOB with default ctx ===

Initial load_model with default args trapped IC0502 "heap out of bounds".
Canister log showed:
  n_ctx = 32768 (model's n_ctx_train default)
  KV buffer = 384 MiB
  compute buffer = 300 MiB
  weights = 531 MiB
  total ≈ 1215 MiB heap allocation

This exceeds the wasm memory pagination budget on SSN even with 3 GB
wasm_memory_limit. Same failure repeated with -c 2048 (compute buffer
still 302 MiB).

Fix: `load_model -c 512 -b 512` → total ≈ 850 MiB, loads cleanly.

This is NEW operational finding: **wasm heap pagination on SSN is
tighter than raw wasm_memory_limit suggests for models >500 MB with
default batch/context sizes.** Affects Phase 3 BitNet 2B4T (~1.8 GB
expected) — will require similar tuning.

=== Measurements ===

Prompt: "The capital of France is"
Load args: --model models/model.gguf --no-warmup -c 512 -b 512

Binsearch:
  N=32 → FAIL
  N=30 → FAIL (local N_MAX)
  N=29 → FAIL
  N=28 → OK, wall=8.98s
  N=26 → OK, wall=8.73s

N_MAX = 28 tok/call

3 reps at N=28:
  rep1: wall=8.89s, output=" ____. A. Paris B. Brussels C. London D. Berlin Answer: A ..."
  rep2: wall=8.89s, output=" ____. A. Paris B. Brussels C. London D. Berlin Answer: A ..."
  rep3: wall=8.71s, output=" ____. A. Paris B. Brussels C. London D. Berlin Answer: A ..."

Byte-determinism across 3 reps: ✓ (identical first 80 chars)
Wall variance: mean=8.83s, stdev=0.10s, CV=1.2%
α_eff SSN = 40e9 / (28 × 2 × 500e6) = 1.429

Notable: output contains "Answer: A" (correct, Paris). Even a non-instruct
base model reliably recalls Paris as France's capital from pretrain.

Cross-env vs local:
  Local (Phase 2 Task 8): N_MAX=30 tok/call
  SSN: N_MAX=28 tok/call
  Delta: -6.7% — larger than SmolLM2's -2% but still within SSN variance
  band observed for prior Qwen measurements

α_eff consistency: local=1.333, SSN=1.429 — within the Paper 1
[1.3, 1.6] modern Q4/Q8 band. No regression.

